materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"4sfh3","text":"- BMG Technologies Omega FLUOstar Reader or similar fluorometer ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c4le","text":"- regular lab equipment (balance, pHmeter, pipetts, tips, tubes)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"arij5","text":"- COSTAR 96-well ELISA plates (Corning, cat# 3916)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ajjii","text":"- MicroAmp Film (Applied Biosystems, cat# 4311971)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e9qri","text":"-  Si3N4 beads 2.38 mm","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":5,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":7,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"76u3g","text":"- molecular biology grade nuclease free water","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eouck","text":"- 0.5 M PIPES pH 6.5","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fhutf","text":"- 5 M NaCl","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aulvf","text":"- Thioflavin T dissolven in water","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e7soo","text":"- recombinant C-terminal His-tag alpha synuclein","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"85g0i","text":"- 1% BSA","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bpnpm","text":"- 5 N NaOH and 1N HCl for pH adjustment","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1ieg4","text":"Reaction mixture is prepared calculating 200 μl per well with the following final concentrations:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f4gmu","text":"0.3 mg/mL recombinant alpha-synuclein","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bukg5","text":"0.5 M NaCl","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"89e0i","text":"100 mM PIPES buffer","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"64hpt","text":"5 μM ThT","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ccns3","text":"Beads are blocked with 1% BSA in 100mM PIPES for 1 hr and washed twice with PIPES.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4nlhu","text":"One bead is placed in each well of the assay plate. 160 μl reaction buffer and 40 μl CSF are carefully pipetted in each well. Samples are assessed in triplicates.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"emtg2","text":"Plate is covered with the film and creases are removed manually.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8va8m","text":"Plate is placed in the plate reader and incubated for 240 hrs at 37 °C in cycles of 1 min shaking at 500rpm, 29 mins incubation and fluorescence measurements are taken after every incubation cycle at 440ex/490emm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"t0c8","text":"A sample is considered positive when it crosses a fluorescence threshold established at 3 standard deviations above baseline. 3/3 wells are positive and negative when 1/3 samples are positive while 2/3 is considered as incoclusive. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9o9un","text":"Relative fluorescence units measured at 490 are plotted versus the time in hours and should present a classical exponantial curve with lag phase and plateau. Kinetics parameters obtained from the curves include maximum fluorescence, time to reach 50% of maximal fluoresence and time to reach the established threshold. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2vhqr","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
